    %h2 Location
    %p.text-center
      %a{ href: "https://www.google.com/maps/place/Broadway+Performance+Hall/@47.6158246,-122.321796,17", target: "_blank" } Broadway Performance Hall<br />1625 Broadway Ave<br />Seattle, WA 98122
    %p This year we are returning to Broadway Performance Hall, located at the northwest corner of Broadway and Pine on Capitol Hill, on the Seattle Central campus.

  .row
    %h3 Venue Accessibility
    %ul
      %li The Broadway Performance Hall has eight reserved spaces for folks with mobility devices, and an ADA compliant elevator providing access to the theater level from the main lobby.
      %li The main entrance on Broadway has no stairs between the street and main lobby inside.
      %li The back entrance on Harvard has three stairs up to reach the main lobby level
      %li Restrooms will be gender-neutral. We request that folks refrain from using urinals in these restrooms.
      %li We are unable to provide ASL interpretation or live captioning this year.
      %li Headsets will be available upon request.
      %li BPH is not a scent-free space.
    %p
      %a{ href: "mailto:hello@osfeels.com", target: "_blank" } Please send us an email
      or speak with any organizer or volunteer during the event if you have any questions or need accommodations.

  .row.confetti.smile
    %h2 How to Get Here
    .option
      %h3 Public Transportation
      %p Metro buses 9, 10, 11, 43, 49, 60, and 84 all have stops within a block of the venue. The venue is also a 5 minute walk from the LightRail and First Hill Streetcar's Capitol Hill stations.
      %p
        The
        %a{ href: "http://tripplanner.kingcounty.gov/", target: "_blank" } King County Trip Planner
        and
        %a{ href: "http://pugetsound.onebusaway.org/", target: "_blank" } OneBusAway
        are helpful public transit resources.

    .option
      %h3 Parking
      %p
        %strong Friday 7/22:
        Most nearby street parking has a two hour maximum, so your best bet is to use one of the many nearby parking lots and
        garages. The most convenient garage to use is about a block east of the BPH, and it has a $10 early bird rate.
        The internet is holding the address of this garage secret, so we'll just give you
        %a{ href: "https://www.google.com/maps/place/Rock+Box", target: "_blank" } this map,
        which points to a particular karaoke establishment of which we are quite fond. The garage is one door to the North of that.
      %p
        %strong Saturday 7/23:
        You will find no better deal or convenience than the
        %a{ href: "https://www.google.com/maps/place/1609+Harvard+Ave,+Seattle,+WA+98122/", target: "_blank" } Harvard Garage
        across the street directly behind the BPH. There’s plenty of space, and it costs $5 for all day/night.

    .option
      %h3 Biking
      %p
        There are a number of public bike racks located nearby, including along Broadway in front of the venue and on the 3rd level of the
        %a{ href: "http://www.seattlecentral.edu/transportation/", target: "_blank" } college's parking garage located at Harvard and Pine.
      %p
        A
        %a{ href: "http://www.prontocycleshare.com/", target: "_blank" } Pronto Station
        is located behind the venue on Harvard and Pine.

  .row.confetti.heart
